President Obama released a statement on the 40th anniversary of Earth Day, acknowledging the efforts of millions of Americans who have worked together to protect the environment. He highlighted the progress made over the past four decades, including landmark legislation such as the Clean Air and Clean Water Acts. The Obama Administration has also invested in clean energy and renewed its commitment to passing comprehensive energy and climate legislation. The President emphasized the importance of people from different backgrounds coming together to work towards a cleaner and safer planet for future generations.